# What the PACKAGED extension ships. The runtime is: dist/ (the bundled
# extension host + webview JS) plus the Python the host spawns at run time
# (producer/*.py, which imports contract/contract.py). Everything else — source
# that's already bundled into dist/, tests, screenshot evidence, fixtures — is
# excluded so the .vsix stays small.

# Screenshot evidence + scale artifacts (regenerated by the test suites).
reports/**
media/**

# Tests and their fixtures (not run inside the installed extension).
tests/**
contract/fixtures/**

# Source already bundled into dist/ (esbuild): the extension host + webview TS.
src/**
webview/**
contract/*.ts
contract/SPEC.md

# Python bytecode caches.
**/__pycache__/**
**/*.pyc

# Build/editor/project cruft not needed at runtime.
.vscode/**
.gitignore
tsconfig.json
*.vsix
producer/CONTRACT_FIT_AUDIT.md
HANDOFF*.md

# Workspace mod examples — .molaro/ is USER-WORKSPACE data (the extension
# loads mods from the opened workspace, not from itself).
.molaro/**
